    "body": "### Problem\n\npressing gx on www.google.com fails with message:\n`vim.ui.open: command failed (1): { \"cmd.exe\", \"/c\", \"start\", \"\", \"www.google.com\" }`\nrunning :lua vim.ui.open(\"www.google.com\") doesn't work either.\nrunning the following worked :!cmd.exe /c start \"www.google.com\"\n\n### Steps to reproduce\nnvim --clean\n:e test\npress gx on \"www.google.com\"\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nopen the url\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.13.0-dev-375+g1e06e95662\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nnot sure\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nwindows 11\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nwindows terminal\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\necho $TERM returned empty string\n\n### Installation\n\nscoop",
