            "body": "> running the following worked :!cmd.exe /c start \"www.google.com\"\n\n`gx` and open() have to decide whether a string is a local file or a URL. It can't assume that \"x.y.z\" is a URL.\n\nWell, I suppose we could assume that `x.y.z` is a URL if not found on the filesystem. But that could lead to unwanted browser navigation for many cases...",
